    <h1 class="opener__hed  -is-over-bg opener__hed--light opener__hed--small" >        Fossil Fuel Interests Are Working to Kill Solar in One Ohio County. The Hometown Newspaper Is Helping.
    </h1>

    
            <div class="article-meta-1  -is-over-bg article-meta-1--light">
            <span class="article-meta-1__byline">
                by <span class="name">Miranda Green</span>, <a href="https://floodlightnews.org/">Floodlight</a>, <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/jennifer-smith-richards">Jennifer Smith Richards</a>, ProPublica, and <span class="name">Priyanjana Bengani</span>, <a href="https://towcenter.columbia.edu/">Tow Center for Digital Journalism</a>, and photography by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/sarahbeth-maney">Sarahbeth Maney</a>, ProPublica            </span>
            <time class="article-meta-1__pubdate">
                <time class="timestamp" datetime="2024-10-08EDT05:00">Oct. 8, 5 a.m. EDT</time>
            </time>
        </div>
    
    </div> <!-- Close .opener__topic-title-dek-wrapper -->

            <div class="content"> <!-- not sure if this is the best way to reestablish the text column -->
            <h2 class="opener__dek opener__dek--match-text-column" style="display: none">                A retired gas industry executive, a shadowy “grassroots” group and a controversial media company are spreading misinformation while turning residents against a proposed solar farm — and each other.
            </h2>
        </div>
    
</div>
        
